#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:3
msgid "OPT4060 driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:6
msgid "1. Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:8
msgid ""
"This driver supports the Texas Instrument RGBW high resolution color sensor "
"over I2C. https://www.ti.com/lit/gpn/opt4060"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:12
msgid ""
"The driver supports: - Raw values for red, green, blue and clear. - "
"Illuminance values. - Scaled color values for red, green and blue. - IIO "
"events for thresholds. - IIO triggered buffer using both its own data ready "
"trigger and triggers from other drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:21
msgid "2. Illuminance calculation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:23
msgid "Illuminance is calculated using the wide spectrum green channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:25
msgid "lux = GREEN_RAW x 2.15e-3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:27
msgid ""
"The value is accessed from: /sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX/"
"in_illuminance_input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:30 ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:61
msgid "See section 8.4.5.2 in the data sheet for additional details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:33
msgid "3. Color scale values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:35
msgid ""
"The sensor has different sensitivity for the different color components and "
"compensating factors are exposed from the driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:38
msgid ""
"The values are accessed from: /sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX/"
"in_intensity_red_scale /sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX/"
"in_intensity_green_scale /sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX/"
"in_intensity_blue_scale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:43
msgid ""
"A userspace application can multiply the raw values with the scale values so "
"that for a particular test light source, typically white, the measurement "
"intensity is the same across the different color channels. This is "
"calculated in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:48
msgid ""
"R = RED_RAW x SCALE_RED(2.4) G = GREEN_RAW x SCALE_GREEN(1.0) B = BLUE_RAW x "
"SCALE_BLUE(1.3)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:52
msgid ""
"The data sheet suggests using the scaled values to normalize the scaled R, G "
"and B values. This is useful to get a value for the ratio between colors "
"independent of light intensity. A userspace application can do this in the "
"following way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/opt4060.rst:57
msgid ""
"R_NORMALIZED = R / (R + G + B) G_NORMALIZED = G / (R + G + B) B_NORMALIZED = "
"B / (R + G + B)"
msgstr ""
